usage: git-config-select --recursive
   or: git-config-select [<options>] [--] [<branch>...]

Configure submodule selection.

    -h|--help               display help
    -r|--recursive          traverse submodules recursively
    -i|--include [SM1,...]  enable  select for specific submodules (default to all) on current branch
    -x|--exclude [SM1,...]  disable select for specific submodules (default to all) on current branch

remarks:    
    By default, level 0 submodules are enabled, others are disabled.

example:
    git-config-select               # display status
    git-config-select -r            # display status recursively
    git-config-select -i            # enable select for all submodules on current branch
    git-config-select -i sm1 sm2    # enable select for submodules sm1 and sm2 on current branch
